Wales
-----
Date: Mon 10 Jun 2013
Source: ITV News [edited]
http://www.itv.com/news/update/2013-06-11/wales-mumps-warning-as-measles-cases-continue-to-rise/


Public Health Wales has warned that cases of mumps are now on the rise, after a month of increasing measles diagnoses. Up to the end of May 2013, there were 76 confirmed cases of mumps in Wales for the year so far; that compares with 77 cases for the whole of 2011 and 88 for the whole of 2012. The measles outbreak centred around Swansea has now seen 1191 cases despite more than 50 000 MMR vaccinations in the area, although the increase in cases has started to slow.

